    • startDateSelected

      public void startDateSelected()

    • submitButtonPressed

      public void submitButtonPressed(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Event handler for when the submit button is pressed. Validates the user's input, and checks if the appointment time isn't fully within business hours. Saves the input into either an appointment update or new appointment.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - the event triggered by pressing the button.

    • cancelButtonPressed

      public void cancelButtonPressed(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Event handler for when the cancel button is pressed. Takes the user back to the main customer/appointment list screen after a confirmation.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - the event triggered by pressing the button.

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      Initialization method called when the form is loaded. Sets time spinners to be reasonably accessible, and if we are modifying an existing appointment, populate the form fields.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url - The URL used to initialize the controller.
      resourceBundle - The ResourceBundle used to initialize the controller.
